2853858.description: Virgilio talks about his first time 'unofficially' volunteering when he was in high school.

2853859.description: Regina talks about how her recent experience volunteering with New York Cares at the Clay Avenue Tenants Association has been very rewarding and supported her ability to expand her skills and network.

2853860.description: One thing Virgilio likes about his Bronx community is the stories he gets to hear from neighbors.

2853861.description: One of Virgilio's community concerns is the increase in local police presence.

2853862.description: One thing that Regina really likes about her community is that everyone is willing to help each other out--she shares a personal story about how this has impacted her family.

2853863.description: Regina talks about the increase in gun and gang violence activity in her community and how she appreciated the policy presence.

2853864.description: Maria and Regina talk about the act of looking out for each other as an important type of community service.

2853865.description: Regina talks about an idea she has to introduce buddy checks with older adults and others who are homebound throughout the community.

2853866.description: Virgilio shares an idea for an event that could bring people together for a block party to share their stories.

2839444.description: It's nice to hear someone directly speak to why kids join gangs.

2853867.description: Regina shares an idea for a community farm that would support agriculture and nutrition education for local youth.

2853868.description: Virgilio talks about the importance of the community stepping up to work directly with New York Cares.

2853869.description: Regina agrees with Virgilio that in order to create a sustainable New York Cares project, the community needs to step in and support it.

2853870.description: Virgilio shares on why some people might hold back from volunteering in their communities.

2853871.description: Virgilio talks about the importance of tiny acts of kindness.
